{"questionId":"9067429","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Propene is an important starting material for many products. The following shows some compounds which can be made from propene, C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><br>Propene (C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>) → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>7</sub>Cl → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O → C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>O</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">An experiment was carried out to determine the order of reaction between one of the isomers of C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>7</sub>Cl and aqueous sodium hydroxide. The following results were obtained.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/b0b224937c0d4702214646de167014db83840fa3.png\" width=\"367\" height=\"138\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Deduce the type of mechanism for the reaction of this isomer of C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>7</sub>Cl with aqueous sodium hydroxide.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">SN2 ✔</span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NOTE: Accept ‘bimolecular nucleophilic substitution.’</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067429","referenceCode":"19N.2.hl.TZ0.3b(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the type of mechanism for the reaction of this isomer of C3H7Cl with aqueous sodium hydroxide.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry","20.1 Types of organic reactions","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}